{% import "product-components.njk" as pc %}
<section class="intro-section mb-12">
  <h3 id="mission">Mission</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Web Lifecycle</strong> standardizes a <strong>domain entity's lifecycle</strong> &mdash; a
    declared set of statuses and the guarded, role-scoped transitions between them. A loan application, an
    insurance policy, a claim, an order, a support ticket: each is a state machine
    (<code>draft &rarr; submitted &rarr; &hellip; &rarr; closed</code>) whose legal moves depend on
    <em>who</em> the actor is and on guard predicates. Today every application re-invents that machine in
    bespoke <code>if (status === &hellip;)</code> code, scattering the transition rules, the permission
    checks, and the status badges across the app.
  </p>
  <p>
    Web Lifecycle fixes one seam &mdash; a <strong>declarative transition map</strong> resolved by a
    swappable <strong>lifecycle provider</strong> &mdash; and nothing else. The map is data, so a workflow
    engine (XState, a BPM server, a hand-rolled reducer) plugs in behind the provider without touching the
    entity. <strong>The transition map is the only lock.</strong>
  </p>

  <div class="comparison-block" style="background: rgba(79, 70, 229, 0.08); padding: 1.25rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #4f46e5; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
    <h4 style="margin-top: 0; color: #4338ca; font-size: 1rem;">Not Web States, not a region's lifecycle</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">
      <a href="/projects/webstates/">Web States</a> owns reactive state <em>primitives</em> (signals,
      stores, change records) &mdash; the mechanism for observing a mutation.
      <a href="/projects/webguards/">Web Guards</a> owns a <em>region's</em> lifecycle (may this route/modal
      tear down or be entered). Web Lifecycle owns the <em>domain object's</em> workflow state: a typed
      status set and the rules for moving an entity between statuses. They compose &mdash; a lifecycle's
      transition is reactive state, and its authorization is a guard &mdash; but they are different layers.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

